1. Download all the files I need from rscb.org.  

2. Find the residue to mutate. 
Helpand: press esc
Helpand: /[chain name]  [resid num]
Helpand: press n (to search forward)
Helpand: press N (to search backward)

3. Select a block of text for the residue name. 
Command: press esc
Command: press v
Command: arrow over the block of text
Command: press d

2. Open files in VMD.
Command: mol new (pdb file name).pdb 

3. Save aligned molecule.
a. Select the molecule. 
Command: set sel [atomselect 0 "chain A"]
b. Make a pdb from the molecule. 
Command: set sel2 [::TopoTools::selections2mol "$sel"]

4. Look at it.  

5. Save pdb. 
Command: animate write pdb (name of pdb).pdb $sel2

6. Move pdb file to where you want it stored.  



 


